            <p> <b> <u> Introduction </u></b> <br>
                Welcome to our guide on cat care basics! Whether you're a long-time cat owner or 
                considering adopting a feline friend, these essential tips will help you provide the best care for your beloved pet.
            </p>
            <p>
                <b> <u> Nutrition </u></b> <br>
                Feed your cat a balanced diet that includes high-quality cat food and plenty of fresh water. Avoid feeding
                them human food, as it can be harmful to their health. 
            </p>
            <p>
                <b> <u> Exercise </u> </b> <br>
                While cats are often independent, they still need opportunities for play and exercise. 
                Provide toys and interactive play sessions to keep your cat mentally and physically stimulated.
            </p>
            <p>
                <b> <u> Grooming </u></b> <br>
                Regular grooming is essential to keep your cat's coat healthy and reduce shedding. Brush their fur, trim
                their nails, and clean their ears and teeth regularly.
            </p>  
            <p>
                <b> <u> Healthcare </u></b> <br>
                Regular vet visits are crucial for your cat's health. Keep up with vaccinations, 
                flea and tick prevention, and dental care. Watch for any changes in behavior or appetite that could signal illness.
            </p>     
            <p>
                <b> <u> Litter Box Maintenance: </u> </b> <br>Litter Box Maintenance:
            Keep your cat's litter box clean by scooping it daily and changing the litter regularly.
            Cats are clean animals and may refuse to use a dirty litter box.
            </p>
            <p>
                <b> <u> Conclusion </u> </b> <br>
                By following these simple tips for cat care, you can ensure that your feline companion enjoys a happy and healthy life with you. With proper nutrition, exercise, grooming, healthcare, 
                litter box maintenance, and environmental enrichment, you'll create a loving and fulfilling relationship with your cat.
            </p>
